&lt;div class="success-icon hx-hidden group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-block hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4">&lt;/div>
&lt;/button>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;h2>2026 technical review&lt;span class="hx-absolute -hx-mt-20" id="2026-technical-review">&lt;/span>
&lt;a href="#2026-technical-review" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;h2>Technical review: budget semantics&lt;span class="hx-absolute -hx-mt-20" id="technical-review-budget-semantics">&lt;/span>
&lt;a href="#technical-review-budget-semantics" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>A PDB does not guarantee that a workload “remains running.” It limits evictions performed through the Eviction API when doing so would exceed the budget. Direct Pod or Deployment deletion can bypass it, involuntary failures cannot be prevented, and a Deployment rollout is governed by its own strategy even though unavailable rollout Pods count towards budget health.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The selector must match the workload&amp;rsquo;s Pods exactly. Set either minAvailable or maxUnavailable, never both. For a single-replica application, minAvailable: 1 blocks voluntary eviction and can prevent a node drain from completing; it cannot create high availability. Add replicas and spread them across failure domains before using a PDB to preserve capacity.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The nested Helm condition in the original example omits minAvailable when pdb exists but minAvailable does not. Prefer a single default expression and validate the values:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx-relative hx-mt-6 first:hx-mt-0 hx-group/code">
&lt;div>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-go-html-template" data-lang="go-html-template">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="cp">{{-&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">$default&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">:=&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">max&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">sub&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">int&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="na">.Values.replicaCount&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">)&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">1&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">)&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">1&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="cp">-}}&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">minAvailable: &lt;span class="cp">{{&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">dig&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s">&amp;#34;pdb&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s">&amp;#34;minAvailable&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">$default&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="na">.Values&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="cp">}}&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;/div>&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx-opacity-0 hx-transition group-hover/code:hx-opacity-100 hx-flex hx-gap-1 hx-absolute hx-m-[11px] hx-right-0 hx-top-0">
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx-group/copybtn hx-transition-all active:hx-opacity-50 hx-bg-primary-700/5 hx-border hx-border-black/5 hx-text-gray-600 hover:hx-text-gray-900 hx-rounded-md hx-p-1.5 dark:hx-bg-primary-300/10 dark:hx-border-white/10 dark:hx-text-gray-400 dark:hover:hx-text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
>
&lt;div class="copy-icon group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-hidden hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4">&lt;/div>
&lt;div class="success-icon hx-hidden group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-block hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4">&lt;/div>
&lt;/button>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>Render with helm template, validate the schema, and test replica counts of zero, one, and several. A percentage or maxUnavailable can track scaled Deployments more naturally, but the correct policy depends on quorum and capacity rather than a universal formula.&lt;/p>
